virtual void GfxCoordinates::addCoordinate (  int32  lat,
int32  lon
)  [pure virtual]
 

Abstract method.

Add new coordinates without specifying the previous ones. O(1) complexity if this is a GfxCoordinates32 object, O(n) complexity if this is a GfxCoordinates16 object where n is the number of coordinates added so far. Use with care! Rather use the other version of addCoordinate().

Parameters:
lat Latitude to add.
lon Longitude to add.

Implemented in GfxCoordinates16, and GfxCoordinates32.

Abstract method.

virtual int32 GfxCoordinates::getLat (  uint32  i  )  const [pure virtual]
 

Abstract method.

Get the i:th latitude without specifying the previous latitude. O(1) complexity if this is a GfxCoordinates32 object, O(i) complexity if this is a GfxCoordinates16 object. Use with care! Rather use getLat( uint32 i, int32 prevLat ) if possible.

Parameters:
i Coordinate number to get.
Returns:
The latitude.

virtual bool GfxCoordinates::getPointOnPolygon (  float64  length,
int &  nbrPassedCoords,
int32 &  lat,
int32 &  lon,
bool  fromFirst = true
)  const [virtual]
 

Abstract method.

Get a coordinate on the polygon that is located length meters from either the first or the last coordinate.

Parameters:
length The number of meters from the first (or last) coordinate to the coordinate to return. Valid values are 0 <= length < getLength().
nbrPassedCoords Outparameter that is set to the number of coordinates that are read past to get (lat, lon).
lat Outparamter that is set to the latitude part of the coordinate that is located on the polygon, length meters from the first or last coordinate.
lon Outparamter that is set to the longitude part of the coordinate that is located on the polygon, length meters from the first or last coordinate.
fromFirst Optional parameter that indicated if the returned coordinate should be located length meters from the first (this parameter set to true) or from the last (this parameter set to false) coordinate.
Returns:
True if the outparameters are set correctly, false otherwise. If set to false, nothing could be said about the outparameters.

Referenced by GfxPolygon::getPointOnPolygon().
